    <h2>Mental Math Tricks for Percentages</h2>
    <p>You do not always need a calculator. These mental math shortcuts let you estimate or calculate percentages quickly in your head.</p>

    <h3>Trick 1: The 10 Percent Foundation</h3>
    <p>Finding 10 percent of any number is easy — just move the decimal point one place to the left. Once you know 10 percent, you can build other percentages from it:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>10 percent of 85:</strong> Move decimal left &rarr; 8.5</li>
      <li><strong>5 percent of 85:</strong> Half of 10 percent &rarr; 8.5 / 2 = 4.25</li>
      <li><strong>15 percent of 85:</strong> 10 percent + 5 percent &rarr; 8.5 + 4.25 = 12.75</li>
      <li><strong>20 percent of 85:</strong> Double 10 percent &rarr; 8.5 &times; 2 = 17.00</li>
      <li><strong>1 percent of 85:</strong> Move decimal left twice &rarr; 0.85</li>
      <li><strong>3 percent of 85:</strong> 1 percent &times; 3 &rarr; 0.85 &times; 3 = 2.55</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Trick 2: The Swap Rule</h3>
    <p>One of the most useful percentage properties is that X percent of Y equals Y percent of X. This means you can swap the numbers to make the calculation easier:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>8 percent of 25</strong> is the same as <strong>25 percent of 8</strong> &rarr; 8 / 4 = 2.00</li>
      <li><strong>4 percent of 75</strong> is the same as <strong>75 percent of 4</strong> &rarr; 4 &times; 0.75 = 3.00</li>
      <li><strong>16 percent of 50</strong> is the same as <strong>50 percent of 16</strong> &rarr; 16 / 2 = 8.00</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Trick 3: The Tipping Shortcut</h3>
    <p>For restaurant tips, here is a fast method for common tip amounts:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>10 percent tip:</strong> Move the decimal one place left. Bill is 67.40 &rarr; tip is 6.74.</li>
      <li><strong>15 percent tip:</strong> Find 10 percent, then add half of that. 6.74 + 3.37 = 10.11.</li>
      <li><strong>20 percent tip:</strong> Find 10 percent and double it. 6.74 &times; 2 = 13.48.</li>
      <li><strong>18 percent tip:</strong> Find 20 percent and subtract 10 percent of the tip. 13.48 - 1.35 = 12.13. Or find 10 percent + 5 percent + 3 percent: 6.74 + 3.37 + 2.02 = 12.13.</li>
    </ul>

